    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>General term for Native North American period and culture dating approximately 200 BCE–500 CE, characterized by a shift of settlement to the interior of North America, an expansion of local and inter-regional trade, finer ceramics, and a shift to more elaborate burial practices for important people.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
